10
00:00:27.880 --> 00:00:29.230
Additive color mixing.

11
00:00:29.230 --> 00:00:32.400
So colors actually start black and
become white as more red, blue,

12
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:34.070
or green are added.

13
00:00:34.070 --> 00:00:36.950
This is used for TVs and
other computer monitors.

14
00:00:38.850 --> 00:00:42.468
Subtractive color mixing actually
start white and as filters are added,

15
00:00:42.468 --> 00:00:44.344
they take on the appearance of color.

16
00:00:44.344 --> 00:00:47.366
So this would be for
printed media like photos and magazines.

17
