it can be a little bit boring.

48
00:02:18.896 --> 00:02:22.890
So if you work in an exciting company or
you're building an exciting product,

49
00:02:22.890 --> 00:02:24.960
maybe you want to pick
a different color palette.

50
00:02:27.720 --> 00:02:30.600
Complementary color palettes
are created by selecting two colors

51
00:02:30.600 --> 00:02:33.490
opposite from each other on the color
wheel so they balance each other out.

52
00:02:37.480 --> 00:02:38.550
Then we have analogous.

53
00:02:38.550 --> 00:02:40.310
So analogous color palettes,

54
00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:43.160
you select three different colors on
the same side of the color wheel.

55
00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:45.360
Triadic is super fun.

56
00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:46.500
This one's a little bit edgier.

57
00:02:47.840 --> 00:02:49.680
It's not done as often I would say, but

58
00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:53.150
